ackModal_main_2530176\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530176\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 07, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nax1665702999276.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nax1665702999276.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nax1665702999276.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nax1665702999276\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n<span class=\"keyword msgnum\">Warning: 1000</span>\n<samp class=\"ph msgph\">Entry <var class=\"keyword varname\">EntryName</var> from model overwrites definition from component. In future Uniface versions, this will be reversed</samp>\n</h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This compiler message is generated in Uniface 9 when duplicate entries are detected in the model and in the component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nax1665702999276__section_ecy_pll_tvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d356148e64\"> Problem </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nax1665702999276__p_d69308e1_d69309e1_d69310e1\">ProcScript inheritance has changed in Uniface 10, from\n        being container-based in Uniface 9, to being module-based in Uniface 10. This has\n        consequences for the inheritance of entries and the order in which entries are compiled into\n        the component.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nax1665702999276__ul_j2z_qll_tvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nax1665702999276__li_d31535e1_d31536e1_d31537e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nax1665702999276__p_d69311e1_d69312e1_d69313e1\">In Uniface 9, entries defined in standard triggers\n            and Local Proc Modules of modeled objects are not inherited if any code is defined in\n            the equivalent local containers.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nax1665702999276__li_d31538e1_d31539e1_d31540e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nax1665702999276__p_d69314e1_d69315e1_d69316e1\">In Uniface 10, the compiler concatenates inherited\n            entries then local entries, per object. If the same entry is found in multiple\n            locations, the last entry encountered is used.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nax1665702999276__section_j2j_rll_tvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d356148e88\"> Resolution </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nax1665702999276__p_d69320e1_d69321e1_d69322e1\">To resolve the issue, review your code and refactor\n        it—move the entry that needs to be compiled to a location where it will be compiled in\n        Uniface 10.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nax1665702999276__note_t34_wll_tvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Note: We recommend that you define entries in the Script container\n        of the component object. This makes it easier to centralize, locate, and maintain these\n        modules.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uoi1665702579370.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entries</a><p>Entries are legacy ProcScript modules defined by the entry ProcScript statement. They can be used as private functions, or they can be executed in response to a call statement.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530176\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530176\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Warning: 1000 Entry EntryName from model overwrites definition from component. In future Uniface versions, this will be reversed Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 07, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Warning: 1000 Entry EntryName from model overwrites definition from component. In future Uniface versions, this will be reversed This compiler message is generated in Uniface 9 when duplicate entries are detected in the model and in the component. Problem ProcScript inheritance has changed in Uniface 10, from being container-based in Uniface 9, to being module-based in Uniface 10. This has consequences for the inheritance of entries and the order in which entries are compiled into the component. In Uniface 9, entries defined in standard triggers and Local Proc Modules of modeled objects are not inherited if any code is defined in the equivalent local containers. In Uniface 10, the compiler concatenates inherited entries then local entries, per object. If the same entry is found in multiple locations, the last entry encountered is used. Resolution To resolve the issue, review your code and refactor it—move the entry that needs to be compiled to a location where it will be compiled in Uniface 10. Note: Note: We recommend that you define entries in the Script container of the component object. This makes it easier to centralize, locate, and maintain these modules. Related Links Entries Entries are legacy ProcScript modules defined by the entry ProcScript statement. They can be used as private functions, or they can be executed in response to a call statement. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}